:::

### Density Plot

#### One Continuous Variable

::: panel-tabset
## R


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
tips |>
    ggplot(aes(x = total_bill))+
    geom_density( size = 1, color = "orangered3"
        #adjust = 0.2
    ) + 
    labs(x = "Total Bill", y = "Density")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](visualization_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-26-3.png){width=90%}
:::
:::


## Python


::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
sns.kdeplot(data = tips, x = "total_bill"
            #,bw_adjust = 0.20
            )
plt.xlabel("Total Bill")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](visualization_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-27-1.png){width=90%}
:::
:::

:::

#### Two Continuous Variables

::: panel-tabset
## R


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
tips |>
    select(1:2) |>
    pivot_longer(cols = everything(), names_to = "types", values_to = "values") |>
    ggplot(aes(x = values, col = types))+
    geom_density(size = 1)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](visualization_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-28-3.png){width=90%}
:::
:::


## Python


::: {.cell}

```{.python .cell-code}
